nelo.dstv.com/2016/04/dj-maphorisa-set-on-conquering-africa-musically/|title=DJ Maphorisa Set on Africa|work=[[Channel O]]|date=8 April 2016|accessdate=8 July 2016}}</ref> As a record producer with a blend of [[house music]] and [[afro pop music|afropop]], he has worked with and has received production credits from several notable artists including [[Wizkid (musician)|Wizkid]], [[Kwesta]], [[Uhuru (music group)|Uhuru]], [[Drake (musician)|Drake]], [[Black Coffee (DJ)|Black Coffee]], [[Major Lazer]], [[Runtown]], [[C4 Pedro]] [[Era Istrefi]], among others.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://genius.com/a/meet-dj-maphorisa-the-south-african-co-producer-of-drakes-one-dance|title=MEET DJ MAPHORISA, THE SOUTH AFRICAN CO-PRODUCER OF DRAKE'S \"ONE DANCE\"|work=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Diep|first=Eric|date=12 April 2016|accessdate=8 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://drum.co.za/celebs/dj-maphorisas-chart-topping-production-on-drakes-album-and-his-new-house-and-car/|title=Dj Maphorisa's chart topping production on Drake's album and his new house and car|work=[[Drum (South African magazine)|DRUM]]|last=Dayile|first=Qhama|date=13 May 2016|accessdate=8 July 2016}}</ref> DJ Maphorisa is presently signed to his record label BlaqBoy Music upon quitting [[Kalawa Jazmee Records]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailysun.co.za/News/Entertainment/DJ-Maphorisa-to-go-at-it-alone-20150906|title=DJ MAPHORISA TO GO AT IT ALONE!|work=[[Daily Sun]]|last=Moganedi|first=Kgomotso|date=13 September 2013|accessdate=8 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n'''Collaborative Albums'''\n\n\u2022 Scorpion King EP (with [[Kabza De Small]]) (2019)\n\n\u2022 The Return of Scorpion Kings (with [[Kabza De Small]]) (2019)\n\n\u2022 Scorpion King Live At Sun Arena (with [[Kabza De Small]]) (2020)\nHdj\n<br />\n=== Singles ===\n*[[Runtown]]\n#[[The Banger]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.tooxclusive.com/downloadmp3/premiere-runtown-banger-ft-uhuru/ | title=PREMIERE: Runtown \u2013 The Banger ft. Uhuru | publisher=tooXclusive | author=Tyler Batimoore | date=9 December 2014 | accessdate=18 August 2015}}</ref>\n#\"Omalicha Nwa\"\n\n*[[Kwesta]]\n#[[Ngud']]\n#\"Mayibabo\"\n#\"Afro Trap\"\n\n*[[Mafikizolo]]\n#[[Khona]]\n#[[Kucheza]]\n#[[Love Portion]]\n\n===Singles produced===\n{{Expand list|date=March 2018}}\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as either producer or co-producer, with selected chart positions and certifications, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! colspan=\"8\" scope=\"col\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Irish Singles Chart|IRL]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Entertainment Monitoring Africa|SA]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B<br>/HH]]<br>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Ngud|Ngud']]\"<br />{{small|([[Kwesta]])}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2016\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|1\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\n* [[Recording Industry of South Africa|RiSA]]: 5x Platinum<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sa-ema.com/local-chart/?week=2016-02-09|access-date=9 July 2016}}</ref>\n|''[[DaKAR II]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[One Dance]]\"<br />{{small|([[Drake (rapper)|Drake]] featuring [[Wizkid 